<title type="html"><![CDATA[3/19  Have you noticed an increase in food prices recently?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=710&amp;p=738#p738"><![CDATA[
3/19 .study, the article and discussions listed below for your <br /><br />1st article <br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://tw.voicetube.com/videos/172059">https://tw.voicetube.com/videos/172059</a><!-- m --><br /> (Why food is getting more expensive for everyone)<br /><br />Discussions ~<br />1)Have you noticed an increase in food prices recently? If so, which foods have you noticed have gone up in price the most?<br />2)What do you think are the main factors contributing to rising food prices?<br />3)Do you think there are differences in the reasons why food prices are increasing in developed versus developing countries? If so, what are they?<br />4)How do you think rising food prices are affecting different populations, such as low-income families, farmers, or small business owners?<br />5)Are there any solutions or strategies you can think of that could help mitigate the effects of rising food prices, either at an individual or societal level?<br /><br />Agenda:<br />7:00-7:10 pm Opening Remarks<br />7:05-7:40 pm Session 1: Group Discussion<br />7:40-8:00 pm Individual Presentation<br />8:00-8:05 pm Break<br />8:05-8:40 pm Session 2: Group Discussion<br />8:40-9:00 pm Individual Presentation<br /><br />We will hold a zoom meeting only.<br /><br />Zoom meeting: Please click the link below<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw">https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw</a><!-- m --> ...<br />Meeting ID:929 8726 6213<br />Password:112233<br /><br />2nd article <br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hK6mdoxXrIc">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hK6mdoxXrIc</a><!-- m --><br />How Perfectionism Makes Us Ill<br /><br />Discussions~<br />1)The article argues that perfectionism can lead to negative physical and mental health outcomes. Have you ever experienced this yourself, or observed it in someone else?<br /><br />2)The article suggests that perfectionism can be caused by a variety of factors, including social pressures, fear of failure, and past experiences. What do you think are some other factors that might contribute to perfectionism?<br /><br />3)The article discusses how perfectionism can lead to anxiety, depression, and other mental health issues. How do you think these negative outcomes can be mitigated or addressed?<br /><br />4)The article suggests that a growth mindset, in which people focus on progress rather than perfection, can be a more positive approach to achieving goals. How do you think this mindset could be cultivated in individuals who struggle with perfectionism?<br /><br />5)The article also suggests that mindfulness and self-compassion can be helpful in reducing the negative effects of perfectionism. Have you ever practiced mindfulness or self-compassion techniques? If so, what benefits have you noticed?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=48">dora</a> — Thu Mar 16, 2023 7:19 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
